The paper discusses a positioning system for self-organizing networks, specifically wireless sensor networks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) category. The paper also proposes a method for building a coordinate system based on nodes' neighborhood knowledge, which involves the use of algorithms and data structures, indicating that the paper may also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) category. The paper also mentions the use of measurements and simulations, which suggests that it may belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) category. The paper discusses the use of Jumps in the context of routing, which suggests that it may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category. Finally, the paper proposes a method for improving the localization process, which involves the use of mathematical techniques, indicating that it may also belong to the Mathematical Aspects of Computer Science (cs.MA) category.
